From: Denis Efremov <efremov@linux.com>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2020 12:32:03 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] io_uring: use kvfree() in io_sqe_buffer_register()
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.7.3
Git-commit: a8c73c1a614f6da6c0b04c393f87447e28cb6de4

commit a8c73c1a614f6da6c0b04c393f87447e28cb6de4 upstream.

Use kvfree() to free the pages and vmas, since they are allocated by
kvmalloc_array() in a loop.

Fixes: d4ef647510b1 ("io_uring: avoid page allocation warnings")
Signed-off-by: Denis Efremov <efremov@linux.com>
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@kernel.dk>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20200605093203.40087-1-efremov@linux.com
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 fs/io_uring.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fs/io_uring.c b/fs/io_uring.c
index 6883104323bd..9a9ae6b4eeac 100644
--- a/fs/io_uring.c
+++ b/fs/io_uring.c
@@ -7093,8 +7093,8 @@ static int io_sqe_buffer_register(struct io_ring_ctx *ctx, void __user *arg,
 
 		ret = 0;
 		if (!pages || nr_pages > got_pages) {
-			kfree(vmas);
-			kfree(pages);
+			kvfree(vmas);
+			kvfree(pages);
 			pages = kvmalloc_array(nr_pages, sizeof(struct page *),
 						GFP_KERNEL);
 			vmas = kvmalloc_array(nr_pages,
-- 
